    {
      "paragraph_name": "4000-FILE-CLOSE",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph closes the output files OPFILE1 and OPFILE2. It displays a message indicating that the files are being closed. It then closes each file and checks the file status (WS-OUTFL1-STATUS and WS-OUTFL2-STATUS). If the close operation fails for either file (status is not spaces or '00'), it displays an error message. This paragraph ensures that the output files are properly closed after processing is complete. It consumes WS-OUTFL1-STATUS and WS-OUTFL2-STATUS. It produces closed output files OPFILE1 and OPFILE2. It does not call any other paragraphs. The paragraph checks the file status after each CLOSE statement and displays an error if the status is not successful, but does not abend.",
